@node intro "Introduction"

@{b}@{u} What is it for?@{ub}@{uu}

	MagicScan  is  a  multifunction  file(scan)  utility  for  DLG  Pro
	BBS-systems.   It  started  as a simple new file scanner but it has
	gained more functions and bigger size since start.

	Main Operation is quite similar as in DDDLister.  Intented usage is
	in  Login-scripts  but  this  can be ofcourse used in anywhere from
	BBS.   (Scripts,  menus..)  It can be used for replacing DDDLISTER,
	SKYSEARCH  and @{"DUPCHECKER" link dupcheck} as MagicScan has also a keyword search, a
	X  days old file scan function, a duplicate check mode and recently
	also a @{"ARCHIVE TESTER." link arctest}

		@{"BIG QUESTION UNDER THIS LINK, CLICK IT :-)" link whymulti}

	Main  reason  I  programmed  this is because @{u}DDDLISTER seems to
	corrupt  memory  in  my  system@{uu}. 
	(It might not be your fault Eric J.  but the SAS/C's fault!)

	The biggest reason, when thinking from your (the poor sysop) side:

@{b}@{fg highlight}
                       THIS IS A FREE PUBLIC DOMAIN PROGRAM
                         NO CHARGE IS REQUIRED WHEN USING
@{ub}@{fg text}

	Though,  I  would  like to receive @{b}a post card@{ub} if you are using
	this regularly :)

	Please look at the @{"HISTORY" link history} for changes and features

@endnode

@node whymulti "New File Scanner can do Archive Testing, eh..?"

 @{b}@{u}Why in the he....@{ub}@{uu}

	Somebody  might  ask  (somebody ALREADY did, Atte :) Why a NEW FILE
	SCANNER  contains  also ARCHECK and DUPCHECK?  

	Well..., WHY NOT?  

	Most  of  the  routines  were  already  present in MagicScan when I
	started  programming  those  extra  bits.   And  why have dozens of
	programs  which  all  do  one  specific task, WHY NOT have a single
	program which can be used for many things!

@endnode

@node require "Requirements"

 @{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

	 OS2.04  required  and  a  working,  properly  installed
	@{"Dialog Pro BBS" link dialog} BBS sofware!

	 It was compiled with SAS/C V6.51 and should work nicely
	without Gurus or Crashes.

@{b}@{u}NOTE!@{ub}@{uu}	Due  to  my BAD programming habit using GLOBAL variables
	MagicScan CAN'T BE MADE RESIDENT!

@endnode

@node dialog "What is DLG?"

 @{b}@{u}Hmm, DLG? What does it mean?@{ub}@{uu}

	 DLG stands for Dialog Professional BB/OS.  It's really amazing
	package  from  Telepro  Technologies.  There's so many features
	within this software so I won't start listing them here.

	 If  you  like  to  know more about DLG.  Call ANY BBS which is
	running with it.  I think you will see what I mean.

@endnode

@node install "Installing CheckAlias"

 @{b}@{u}Great, But How do I install it?@{ub}@{uu}

	Here's STEP-BY-STEP instructions:

	1) Take a deep breath!

	2) Consider twice do you need this program!

	3) Make a barrel of coffee, and drink it!

 almost 4) :) Decide do you want to use a 68030 or plain 68000
	   version

	4) Copy the executable "MagicScan" to some directory
	   where you keep your 3rd party DLG utils.

	   eg.	Copy MagicScan DLGOWN:

	   (I use secondary assign and directory for third party
	    DLG utilities)

	5)  Place it for example to the LOGIN.DLGBATCH script so
	    users can scan new files every time they log on!

		Check for @{"OPERATIONAL PARAMETERS" link paramet}

@endnode

@node paramet "Calling Parameters & Operation"

 @{b}@{u}Parameters passed to MagicScan in Commandline@{ub}@{uu}

	There  are  LOTS  of parameters!  Do not be confused about them,
	actually  you don't need ANY parameters.  But I suggest that you
	read  the  descriptions and decide the best combination for you.
	You can also look for the examples I have put in this document.

	Parameters can be in any order!  All parameters are optional, if
	no  parameters  are  specified  then the default operation is to
	scan  new files without asking anything, comparing filepointers.
	In default operation, filepointers will not be updated!

	@{fg highlight}@{b}MagicScan <parameters>@{fg text}@{ub}

@{u}Normal Parameters:@{uu}

	@{u}?@{uu}	Command line parameter help

	@{u}-a@{uu}	Causes MagicScan to ask if user wants to scan
		for new files, x days old files or search keyword

	@{u}-b@{uu}	Suppress all credits! And program version info!

	@{u}-p@{uu}	Instead  of  comparing  filepointers, compare dates.  If
		file  has  been uploaded after user has called last time
		it will be displayed as new.

		If filedates are messy, then this won't naturally work!

		Look @{"history" link history} for explaining of this flag.

	@{u}-h@{uu}	Hide areas if user has no pointers for the file area

	@{u}-g@{uu}	Will   Scan   only   areas   which  user  has  selected!
		(GlobalAreas.FILE)

	@{u}-s<X>@{uu}	Scan only areas defined SIG <X>

	@{u}-u@{uu}	Update filepointers during new file scan. 
		(default is to NOT UPDATE!)

	@{u}-0@{uu}	If  you  as a sysop want to scan only the areas you have
		selected  in  your global file areas, then specify this!
		If  not  specified,  sysops  level users (255) will scan
		every area in BBS.

@{fg highlight}|---<@{fg text}	@{u}-d@{uu}	Set operation mode automagically to 
@{fg highlight}|@{fg text}		'SCAN X DAYS OLD FILES' and ask for day count.
@{fg highlight}|
@{fg highlight}|---<@{fg text}	@{u}-k@{uu}	Set operation mode automagically to 
@{fg highlight}|@{fg text}		'KEYWORD SEARCH' and ask for keyword
@{fg highlight}|@{fg text}
@{fg highlight}|----->@{fg text}	If  you  want to set operation mode with -d or -k, use only one
	of them, NOT BOTH :) (No harm, but it does not work)

@{u}DupChecker mode:@{uu}		@{"DUPCHECKING FILES" link dupcheck}

	@{u}-fFILE@{uu}	Check  for  duplicate  files.  Filename must be after -f
		parameter. (-fFILENAME.LHA)

		If  you leave the filename out, then MagicScan will work
		in    MULTICHECK    mode,    all   uploaded   files   in
		"File:TempUploads/User_Name/" will be scanned!

	@{u}-n@{uu}	Ignore filename extensions when checking duplicates.

	@{u}-oNAME@{uu}	User to inform for DUPLICATES.  Place your name here.
		(-oErno_Tuomainen) If you leave this out, MagicScan will
		inform only the user. THIS MUST BE CONFIGURED!

	@{u}-eX@{uu}	End  duplicate  check  if X duplicates found.  X must be
		between 1 and 50. @{fg shine}Default is 10@{fg text}

		(In  MULTICHECK  mode  this  works  as  X DUPLICATES PER
		CHECKED FILE!)

	@{u}-mX@{uu}	How  to  inform  Sysop  (specified  with -oUSR) if dupes
		found.  X can have these values! @{fg shine}Default is 1@{fg text}:

			@{b}1@{ub}	inform by writing to @{u}EVENT.LOG@{uu}
			@{b}2@{ub}	inform by writing a @{u}PVT message@{uu}
			@{b}3@{ub}	@{u}BOTH of the above@{uu}

	@{u}-c@{uu}	Don't check private uploads.

	@{u}-lX@{uu}	Minimum user level for Duplicate Check.  Default is 255.
		Set this to 254 if you don't want that Sysop uploads are
		checked.

	@{u}-i@{uu}	Bonus! Inform online users about new uploads!

	@{u}-jX@{uu}	Specify the stack size for running external executables.
			Default is 40000 bytes.

	@{u}-x@{uu}	Enable Archive Test!

@{u}@{b}NOTE!!!@{uu}@{ub}	@{fg highlight}If user is a sysop (Level = 255) then MagicScan
	scans always EVERY FILE AREA!!!!@{fg text}

	This  program  must be run ON-LINE!  Either from menu or
	some  script.   It  takes  all the needed stuff directly
	from DLG with couple of dlg.library calls.

		@{" Examples  " link examples} @{u}Hit here for examples@{uu}

	@{b}If you want to run MagicScan from a menu@{ub}

		@{" MenuEntry " link menuentry} @{u}Hit here for example menu entry@{uu}

@endnode

@node menuentry "Example Menu Entry for MagicScan"

 @{u}Example Menu Entry.@{uu}

 	    [ 1] Letter:                   N
	    [ 2] Executable: (path/name)   dlgown:MagicScan -a -g
	                                    -p -s%File_SigNumber
	    [ 4] Description:              Scan for New files
	    [ 5] Type:                     Executable
	    [ 6] Help File:                FILE_MAIN/N
	    [ 7] Lower level:              1
	    [ 8] Upper level:              255
	    [ 9] Hidden:                   NO
	    [10] Load type:                OVERLAY
	    [11] Ask user if sure:         NO
	    [12] Pend messages:            YES
	    [13] Cli mode:                 NO
	    [14] Pause on completion:      NO
	    [15] Log value:                None
	    [16] Activity string:          
	    [17] Priority:                 DEFAULT
	    [18] Edit help file

@endnode

@node examples "Some examples"

 @{b}@{u}Some Examples@{ub}@{uu}

@{u}MagicScan@{uu}

	Default  operation.   Display  small  credit banner when
	starting and start scanning files automagically.

	Scan all areas where users level is allowed to enter
	(autoaccess level)

@{u}MagicScan -a@{uu}

	Same  as  above, but user will be queried if (s)he wants
	to scan for new files.  There is 3 options currently:

	Y	default, scan for new files
	n	abort, do not scan
	*	Instead of scanning new files, user can specify
		a date count (how many days ago file was uploaded)
	d	Scan for X days old files
	s	Keyword Search
	?	Small help

@{u}MagicScan -a -b -u@{uu}

	Same as above, do not show any credits. Update pointers
	in  new file scan mode.

@{u}MagicScan -a -b -g -p@{uu}

	Same  as above.  Additionally check each area from users
	"globalareas.file".   Compare dates instead of pointers.

@{u}MagicScan -d -g -p -s1@{uu}

	Scan for X Days old files. From SIG 1 only!

@{u}MagicScan -k -g -p -s%File_SigNumber@{uu}

	Search for keyword. Scan only from FileSig where
	User currently is.

@{u}MagicScan -fFILENAME.LHA -n -oJohn_Johnsson@{uu}

	Check  if  file  "FILENAME#?"  exists in some area.  And
	inform user "Erno_Tuomainen" if duplicates found.

@{u}MagicScan -fFILENAME.LHA -s1 -oJohn_Johnsson -i -c -m2@{uu}

	Check  if file "FILENAME.LHA" exists in some area.  Scan
	areas   in   SIG  1  only.   Inform  John  Johnsson  for
	duplicates  (with  a  PVT message).  Don't check private
	uploads.

	Send a node message to ALL online users if uploaded file
	is NEW (Not duplicate)

@{u}MagicScan -f -oErno_Tuomainen -n -i -c -m3 -l254 -e2 -x@{uu}

	This  is  what  I  use.   Check duplicates in MultiCheck
	mode,  SCAN  ALL  UPLOADED  files  ONCE  and ignore file
	extensions  in  the scan.  Inform online users about NEW
	uploads.   Don't  check  private  files.  Send a private
	message   and   Event.LOG-entrt   to  me  if  there  was
	duplicates.   Scan  all  users  execpt  level 255).  End
	duplicate  scan  if  2  duplicates  per checked file are
	found. And ARCHIVE TESTing is enabled (-x) too.

@{u}MagicScan ?@{uu}

	Display a small help

@endnode

@node arctest "Testing archive integrity"

@{b}@{u}Testing archive integrity@{ub}@{uu}

	YES!   By  request I have added this too, it was easy to
	add (thanks to duplicate check routines!) 

	When  enabled with -x MagicScan tests uploaded archives.
	You  must  configure  all the archives you need to test.
	This can be done in DLG's sysop menu (General/Archives)

	DupChecker mode is needed for this to work.

@{b}CAUTION!@{ub}

	If you experience mysterious crashes while doing archive
	testing,   try   incerasing   the  stack  size  with  -j
	parameter.  If this does not help, @{"report IMMEDIATELY" link author} to
	me and stop using ArchiveTest for a while.

@endnode

@node dupcheck "Checking duplicate files"

 @{b}@{u}Checking duplicate files with MagicScan@{ub}@{uu}

	YES!  It's possible now. There are EIGHT new @{"parameters" link paramet}
	for this.  (FORGET Program called DUPCHECKER :-)

Quick Setup:

	Edit   your   @{u}DLGCONFIG:BATCH/UPLOAD1.BATCH@{uu}  to  contain
	following:

	@{"EACH FILE ONE BY ONE" link onebyone}		@{"ALL UPLOADED FILES ONCE" link allonce}

	As  you  notice  there  is 2 ways to do this.  Check the
	links aboce for full description.

@endnode

@node onebyone "DupCheck Setup - One by One"

 @{b}@{u}Upload1.batch for checking file one by one@{ub}@{uu}

	Normally  this  would  be  the  only way to do duplicate
	check.   This  way,  MagicScan  is  forced to scan for a
	specific file.  (specified -f"<file>" parameter.).  This
	means  also  that  MagicScan  will  be executed FOR EACH
	upload  and  the  uploads  are  all  scanned ONE BY ONE.
	Slow, eh... There is a @{"better method" link allonce}!

@{fg highlight}---CUT---@{fg text}
.key username,filename
.bra {
.ket }

DLGOWN:MagicScan.030 -f"{filename}" -n -oErno_Tuomainen -i -m2 -e2 -l254 -c
@{fg highlight}---CUT---@{fg text}
@endnode

@node allonce "DupCheck Setup - All Uploads "

 @{b}@{u}Upload1.batch for checking all uploads in ONE CALL@{ub}@{uu}

	THIS  IS  *THE  BETTER METHOD*!  MagicScan will dupcheck
	ALL  uploaded files ONCE.  It will first scan the upload
	directory for files and then scan ALL FILES FOUNDED.

	Note  that  the  only  change in upload1.batch is the -f
	parameter (it has NO filename) That means that MagicScan
	should  scan  the  upload directory and scan all founded
	files.

@{fg highlight}---BEGIN Upload1.BATCH---@{fg text}
.key username,filename
.bra {
.ket }

DLGOWN:MagicScan.030 -f -n -oErno_Tuomainen -i -m2 -e2 -l254 -c
@{fg highlight}----END Upload1.BATCH.---@{fg text}

	You  will  also  need  to change your UPLOAD function in
	File_Main-menu.   It  must  be  a  MENUSCRIPT and do the
	following:

@{fg highlight}---BEGIN UploadFile.BATCH---@{fg text} 		@{"WHY THIS?" link whychange}
EXE Dlgown:Deletevar %PORT_SCANNED
BUILTIN File_Upload
@{fg highlight}----END UploadFile.BATCH----@{fg text}

 @{b}@{u}Here is the menu setup for changed Upload-function.@{ub}@{uu}

[ 1] Letter:                   U
[ 2] Menu script: (path/name)  dlgconfig:batch/UploadFile.batch
[ 3] Edit file:
[ 4] Description:              Upload file(s)
[ 5] Type:                     Menu script
[ 6] Help File:                FILE_MAIN/U
[ 7] Lower level:              5
[ 8] Upper level:              255
[ 9] Hidden:                   NO
[10] Load type:                OVERLAY
[11] Ask user if sure:         NO
[12] Pend messages:            YES
[13] Cli mode:                 NO
[14] Pause on completion:      NO
[15] Log value:                None
[16] Activity string:          Uploading a File
[17] Priority:                 2
[18] Edit help file

@endnode

@node whychange "Why ?"
 
 @{b}@{u}Why I need to change UPLOAD function?@{ub}@{uu}

	If  MagicScan works in MULTICHECK mode it sets an GLOBAL
	ENVIRONMENT  VARIABLE  to  indicate  that  the files are
	already  checked  in  the  port  user  is  in.   If this
	variable  is  not  deleted  MagicScan does not check new
	uploads until a NEW USER is logged into that PORT.

	(Each  port  has  it's  own  variable  and  it's name is
	%PORT_SCANNED, ie.  TR0_SCANNED.) 

	I  have  included  a  small  program I made for deleting
	Global  Variables  from ENV:  It does NOT print anything
	out,  NOT  even  an error messages.  It just deletes the
	environment    varialbe    with   a   dos.library   call
	"DeleteVar()". Fast and easiest way.

@endnode

