@node history "Program History"

What does it mean?

(RELD)	Released to public.
( ADD)  Something was added into the program.
(FIXD)  Something nasty was fixed.
(BUGN)  Bug noticed but NOT fixed, because I'm lazy too.
(RMVD)	Something was removed
(CHNG)  Something was changed in the soul of program...

 @{b}@{u}Short Version History@{ub}@{uu}

VERSION: (@{b}V1.10 24.08.1994@{ub}) - Nice day, but cold...

	@{"( ADD)" link dupcheck}	Updated  Duplicate  Checker mode a bit or two.  Now it's
		possible  to CHECK ALL uploads by ONE call to MagicScan!
		YES!   No  need  to  scan  each file one by one like old
		DupChecker or previous MagicScan did.
	@{"( ADD)" link arctest}	Archive Check mode.  Currently works only with Duplicate
		Check mode.  Can be enabled with -x parameter.
	( ADD)	-c switch, don't check private uploads
	( ADD)  -lX option, X=max user level to check.
	( ADD)	-jX   option,  specify  the  stack  size  while  running
		ARCHIVERS in ArcTest mode. (default 40000)
	( ADD)	Descriptions   will   also   be   written/displayed   in
		DupChecker mode
	( ADD)	-h  switch.   Hide  all  files  if  user  has  no pointers
		information for the area.

VERSION: (@{b}V1.07 16.08.1994@{ub}) - Updating updating...

	@{"( ADD)" link dupcheck}	Completely new mode of operating. DUPLICATE CHECK
		I added following parameters for that mode:
			-fF   DupChecker Mode, F=FILENAME
			-n    DupChecker ignores extensions
			-eX   End DupScan if X files found (def.10)
			-oUSR User to inform about duplicates
			-mX   Inform sysop how (X=MODE) (def.1)
			      1=Event Log, 2=Message, 3=Both
			-i    Inform online users about new uploads
	( ADD)	When  doing  global  search, matched keyword will now be
		UPPERCASED and highlighted with different color.
	(CHNG)	When  doing  NEW  SCAN  and  MagicScan  can't  find  any
		pointers  for  some  file  area, it will start comparing
		DATES in that file area...
		(Before  MagicScan  did show every file as a new in that
		area)
	(CHNG)	MagicScan  won't  strip > #127 characters  from the file
		description anymore. (Only < #32)

VERSION: (@{b}V1.06 01.08.1994@{ub}) - 03:12 AM :-) This takes time

	(RELD)	Second Release. 
	(FIXD)	A  Bug which would cause lockups in some cases.  That is
		if  some  file  was  0  bytes  long.   Should not happen
		anymore.

VERSION: (@{b}V1.05 31.07.1994@{ub}) - Night breeds darkly

	( ADD)	@{"-0 parameter" link paramet}
		Specify,  if  you (sysop) want to scan only global areas
		Default is to scan all areas if user is a Sysop.
	( ADD)	@{"-u parameter" link paramet}
		Specify,  if  you want to update pointers while scanning
		NEW  files!   Pointers will be updated when scanning new
		files  in either date or pointer compare mode.  Pointers
		will  not be updated when scanning for KEYWORD or X DAYS
		OLD FILES!
	(CHNG)	The  operation  of  -p parameter.  If -p is specified in
		commandline  then  new file scan will compare users LAST
		CALL  DATE  and  FILE  UPLOAD  DATE  together.   Not any
		pointers. 

		Comparing pointers does cause some problems, because DLG
		does  not  create pointer information to the user before
		he/she has visited the file area first!

		If  -p  is  not specified and some area does not contain
		any  pointer information for the user, all files will be
		displayed  as  new  in  that area.  I suggest you use -p
		option.

	(CHNG)	Speeded up the new file scanning routines.  (It's really
		fast if -p is used!)
	(FIXD)	A  VERY OLD BUG!  It has been in MagicFile since keyword
		search  routine  too.   It sometimes loosed the track of
		all  matched files, in some situations this caused "FILE
		DOES NOT EXISTS" warnings when tagging.  Now it works!
	(FIXD)	If  you  try search with empty keyword -> operation will
		be cancelled.
	(FIXD)	Fixed output a bit.

VERSION: (@{b}V1.04 26.07.1994@{ub}) - Sunlight sunlight, bright morning

	( ADD)	Now also supports sigs.
		added @{"-s parameter" link paramet} for that
	(CHNG)	Moved keyword search to -k parameter.

VERSION: (@{b}V1.03 26.07.1994@{ub}) - Hard work

	(CHNG)	Changed output a bit or two
	(RELD)	@{b}Released to public@{ub}

VERSION: (@{b}V1.02 25.07.1994@{ub}) - New ideas, new day

	( ADD)	New function, scan X days old files 
		Added @{"-d switch" link paramet} !
	( ADD)	New  function,  keyword  search  Because  it needed only
		couple  extra  lines  of C-code I added a keyword search
		too :)
		Added @{"-s switch" link paramet} !

VERSION: (@{b}V1.01 24.07.1994@{ub}) - I am a night being

	( ADD)	Added @{"-p switch" link paramet} !
	( ADD)	Added @{"-g switch" link paramet} !
	(CHNG)	Changed ANSI-display to look better
	(FIXD)	Fixed couple of odd bugs :)

VERSION: (@{b}V1.00 24.07.1994@{ub}) - I am a night being

	( ADD)	Range Tagging, you can enter number strings like:

		1 3-10 12 15-20

	( ADD)	Added 's'-key SKIP AREA

VERSION: Pre V1.00 - nothing to mention about

@endnode

